page.title: 12The Railway-Bolton-le-Sands
page.content: The railway has electric wires for electric trains. However, many diesel trains also use the line. The lines go in a north/south direction. There are supports holding six electric wires. Each support has numbers on it. There is a tunnel for road {transport}to go through under the railway and the lines go over the top. The embankment is about three metres high. On one side of the line there are hawthorn bushes and on the other there are brambles. At the foot of the embankment there is a stream. Next to the stream there are gardens of the nearby bungalows. At the southern end there are some caravans on one side and houses on the other. There are some signals close to the houses.
